member.summary:
Implementation of scaled voice connection using SIP/RTP (Kamailio + RTPEngine).


Usage:


// When VoiceTierUpgradeClientEvent is received:
var connection = new ScaledVoiceConnection(roomId);
connection.OnAudioFrameReceived += (samples, rate, channels) => PlayAudio(samples, rate, channels);
connection.OnConnected += () => Console.WriteLine("Connected to voice conference!");

var credentials = SipConnectionCredentials.FromEvent(event.SipCredentials, event.ConferenceUri);
await connection.ConnectAsync(credentials, event.RtpServerUri);

// Send audio from microphone:
connection.SendAudioFrame(microphonePcm, 48000, 1);

// When leaving the room:
await connection.DisconnectAsync();

Helper class for managing SIP registration with Kamailio in scaled voice tier.


Purpose:

Handles the SIP REGISTER flow with Kamailio server using credentials
provided by the . Manages registration
lifecycle including initial registration, re-registration, and de-registration.



Usage Pattern:


var helper = new SipRegistrationHelper();
helper.OnRegistered += () => Console.WriteLine("Registered!");
helper.OnRegistrationExpiring += (secs) => Console.WriteLine($"Expires in {secs}s");
await helper.RegisterAsync(credentials, cancellationToken);
// ... use voice connection ...
await helper.UnregisterAsync();

             High-level manager for voice chat in a Bannou voice room, supporting both P2P and scaled modes.


             Stride Integration Example:

             // In your NetworkManager or VoiceController script:
             var voiceManager = new VoiceRoomManager(bannouClient);
             voiceManager.OnAudioReceived += (peerSessionId, samples, rate, channels) =>
             {
                 // Play audio via Stride's DynamicSoundSource
                 PlayAudioFromPeer(peerSessionId, samples, rate, channels);
             };

             // In your game loop, send microphone audio:
             voiceManager.SendAudioToAllPeers(microphoneSamples, 48000, 1);




             Automatic Tier Transition:

             When 6+ participants join, the server sends a .
             This manager automatically:


Closes all P2P connections

Connects to the SIP/RTP infrastructure using provided credentials

Redirects audio through the RTP server

             The SendAudioToAllPeers method works transparently in both modes.



             Note: Video is NOT supported in multi-peer scenarios. Use 
             for 1:1 video calls only.
